posts.content:
I know these have been made, bought & sold on here and there are lots of threads about them.Seem to have missed out as I have pm'd a few people that had or made them. Still not luck.

Anyone know if Monkeydub still makes them or anyone else?
So no-one does these then, or has one?

Sadly they are very hard to find...
I have a three and a four bow version...and a home made rear version...
Took me eight years to find them...
But as vwed says they are out there...
Keep looking..
Maddy found one..

I know monkey dub got the tooling set up to make a run as a speculative venture. He advertised and took orders and supplied in a range of materials.
One of the issues with small volume manufacture is if you offer lots of variety everyone wants a different version!
Maybe he did not sell all of the first run and ended up selling on ebay.
Not sure if he lost or made money..
Maybe get a list going to present him with " firm" customers.
Sure you could find his prices or ask him what batch size he would need.
Those that bought were pleased..
.?????????
Tried sending a PM but did not get a reply

He does lots of things...try several avenues to get him..
i did eventuall get a reply!

May be others who want to buy!

Just an fyi I contacted him and got an email back from a colleague saying that they didn't make any money in the end and they were more trouble than it was worth.
They sold the remaining racks at BB and via eBay.
I then asked about who he got to build them and the jig he made but got no further reply.
Hence going to the USA for mine.

Nice work..
I spoke to your contact years ago!
But I did not know he continued and now builds these...
Good work!
I want clamps!

Cheers.
He'll do the clamps separately for you $50 each.
the top part of the clamp is steel. the bolt inside is zinc plated. the bottom part that twists is stainless (with the hole drilled in it) the threaded part is zinc plated. the rest is stainless except the clamp that goes on the gutter.

Where's your thread on your racks?
I can't find it
Ah found them, in the monkey dub post!

Yes....I think I was searching for one and I posted lots of posts looking for a curved dormobile rack.

I am now ordering clamps from the source above!

Thanks

G
